content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and provide a detailed solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
The structure consists of two distinct parts:
1. A taller tower-like structure with:
   - Orange cylindrical pillars at the base
   - Yellow rectangular supports
   - Green rectangular pillars in the middle
   - An orange triangular roof

2. A smaller house-like structure with:
   - A blue cubic base
   - An orange triangular roof
   - Standing on a yellow rectangular platform
   - Orange cylindrical supports underneath

Total layers: 4 layers in the taller structure, 2 layers in the smaller structure

Block Selection and Assembly Order:
{
    Step1: Move block 8 (orange cylinder - left base of tall structure)
    Step2: Move block 8 (orange cylinder - right base of tall structure)
    Step3: Move block 5 (yellow rectangular support - bottom of tall structure)
    Step4: Move block 8 (orange cylinder - left support of small structure)
    Step5: Move block 8 (orange cylinder - right support of small structure)
    Step6: Move block 7 (yellow rectangular platform - for small structure)
    Step7: Move block 3 (green vertical pillar - left side of tall structure)
    Step8: Move block 3 (green vertical pillar - right side of tall structure)
    Step9: Move block 6 (yellow rectangular support - middle of tall structure)
    Step10: Move block 1 (blue cube - base of small house)
    Step11: Move block 5 (yellow rectangular support - top of tall structure)
    Step12: Move block 15 (orange triangular roof - for tall structure)
    Step13: Move block 15 (orange triangular roof - for small house)
}

This assembly sequence builds both structures from bottom to top, ensuring stability throughout the construction process.
